install homebrew package manager : /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

search apps in homebrew : brew search <app_name>

install app using homebrew : brew install <app_name>

check folder size from terminal : du -sh <folder_path>

get IP address : ipconfig getifaddr en0

open an app : open -a <app_name>.app

get current working directory : pwd

list all items in current directory : ls

list all items in current directory, including hidden files: ls -a

to create new directory : mkdir <dir_name>

delete a directory : rmdir <dir_name>

copy a file to a specified directory : cp <file_name> <dir_name>

copy a file to the current directory and rename : cp <file_name> <newfile_name>

delete a file : rm <file_name>

move or rename a file to a new location or name : mv <file_name> <newfilename_name>

see current environment variables : printenv or env

create a conda environment : conda create -n <env_name> python=x.x

remove conda environment : conda remove -n <env_name> --all
